<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0970 </DOCNO><TEXT>A process for removing organic compounds from a nuclear waste slurry comprisingreacting a mixture of radioactive waste precipitate slurry and an acidin the presence of a catalytically effective amount of a copper(II) catalystwhereby the organic compounds in the precipitate slurry are hydrolyzedto form volatile organic compounds which are separated from the reactingmixture. The resulting waste slurry, containing less than 10 percentof the original organic compounds, is subsequently blended with highlevel radioactive sludge land transferred to a vitrification facilityfor processing into borosilicate glass for long-term storage. 2 figs.,3 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>